LARDD 1
TITLE LardOS Driver Branch
TEXT User-installable driver catalog for LardOS.
SECTION Formats
ITEM DRFL is the native driver descriptor format.
ITEM RXR bundles a DRFL descriptor with a small RXE helper app so users can install drivers with rxr install.
ITEM LARDD documents drivers in a LardOS-native readable form.
SECTION Folders
ITEM network -> network adapters.
ITEM storage -> disk and controller descriptors.
ITEM display -> display and framebuffer descriptors.
ITEM input -> keyboard, mouse, and pointer descriptors.
ITEM usb -> USB controller and device descriptors.
ITEM vm -> virtual-machine helper descriptors.
ITEM bundles -> combined packs for common setups.
ITEM tools -> small in-tree helper tools.
SECTION Install
ITEM Put a wanted .rxr on A: or Z:.
ITEM rxr verify A:core-drivers.rxr
ITEM rxr install A:core-drivers.rxr
ITEM drivers reload
ITEM drivers
ITEM sync
ITEM Restart if the descriptor must be present during early boot probing.
SECTION Honesty
ITEM DRFL describes hardware and selects an in-kernel driver name. It is not a hidden external blob.
ITEM If the running kernel does not include the actual driver code, the descriptor stays planned or source-only.
END
